The paper proposes a system that utilizes wireless sensor networks and unmanned aerial vehicles for animal monitoring. The system involves path planning for the UAV based on a Markov decision process model. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves wireless sensor networks and data gathering, which suggests that it could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Q-learning, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves computer vision techniques for animal detection, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves control and decision-making for the UAV, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
